      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Checkpointing too infrequently: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "if checkpointing only at phase boundaries and a phase takes 30 min, a crash mid-phase restarts 15 min of work. Checkpoint after every batch instead.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not idempotent within a phase: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "re-running a batch that was partially written to the vector DB can create duplicates. Track inserted IDs and skip already-stored chunks.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fan-out without rate limiting: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "firing 1,000 asyncio.create_task() at once saturates the Anthropic rate limit. Always batch with asyncio.gather on fixed-size slices.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Storing large intermediate data in Redis: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "embeddings are large (e.g. 1536 floats \u00d7 float32 \u00d7 10K chunks \u2248 60MB). Store them to S3 or Postgres BYTEA, keep only the reference in Redis.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Forgetting to clear the checkpoint on success: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "a completed job that still has a stale checkpoint may confuse a re-triggered run into resuming from a random point.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The key insight for long-running jobs is: treat every phase as independently resumable. Checkpoint after every batch, load the checkpoint at startup, and verify idempotency before writing results. With those three properties in place, worker restarts become routine operational events rather than data-loss incidents."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
